headline: Did TD Cowen’s Reaffirmed Optimism on “One Coach” Just Shift Tapestry’s (TPR) Investment Narrative?
summary: Recently, TD Cowen reaffirmed its positive view on Tapestry after meetings with the CEO and CFO, highlighting stronger evergreen product mix and record fiscal 2026 first-quarter results that beat forecasts. The firm also underscored Coach’s 21% revenue increase and progress under the “One Coach” approach, even as Kate Spade remains a work-in-progress. headline: 3 Reasons to Sell TPR and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Tapestry currently trades at $109.27 and has been a dream stock for shareholders. It’s returned 273% since December 2020, more than tripling the S&P 500’s 85.5% gain. The company has also beaten the index over the past six months as its stock price is up 38.8% thanks to its solid quarterly results.
